
Run deploy.sh to build a scrapers-ca Docker environment for development.

Ideally we'd pass the scrapers-ca Git clone path to deploy.sh, but for now
replace "/your/local/path/to/scrapers-ca" in docker-compose.yml with your
local scrapers-ca's Git clone directory (must be an absolute path).

The following steps need to be automated. For now, run them manually:

# ssh into the Docker environment:
docker-compose exec scrapers-ca /bin/bash
cd scrapers-ca

# PostgreSQL:
service postgresql start
sudo -u postgres createuser root
sudo -u postgres psql -c 'ALTER USER root WITH SUPERUSER;'
sudo -u postgres psql -c "ALTER USER root WITH PASSWORD 'root';"
sudo -u postgres createdb pupa
sudo -u postgres psql pupa -c "CREATE EXTENSION postgis;"
# Pupa:
pupa dbinit ca
# Virtual Environment:
mkvirtualenv scrapers-ca --python=`which python3`
pip install -r requirements.txt
# You can now run your scraper. Ex: pupa update ca_on_candidates
